# QuietNight Structure

- **app/** — Expo Router routes and screens. One screen per file; thin, delegate to hooks and lib.
- **hooks/** — Custom hooks (e.g. `use-system-checks.ts`, `use-room-noise-test.ts`). One concern per hook.
- **lib/** — Storage, nights API, recordings (file helpers), formatters. No UI. Used by hooks and screens.
- **types/** — Shared TypeScript types (e.g. `SnoreEvent`, `CheckStatus`). Re-export from `types/index.ts`.
- **constants/** — `theme.ts` (design tokens), `app.ts` (storage keys, thresholds).
- **components/** — Reusable UI only.

**Where to add:**
- New screen → `app/` (appropriate route).
- New hook → `hooks/` (e.g. `use-foo.ts`).
- New storage/formatting helper → `lib/` (e.g. `lib/nights.ts` or `lib/formatters.ts`).
- New shared type → `types/` (e.g. `types/night.ts` or `types/index.ts`).
